commit_message:
Update repository after OpenStack migration

* Add .gitignore
* Update .gitreview (we thought it would be on Stackforge, but finally
  it's on OpenStack)
* Add .testr.conf
* Update run-flake8 script to avoid error when running flake8 without
  elements.
* Update setup.cfg with correct name & description
* Add no_dup_filenames unit test (required to have py27 gate working)

Change-Id: Iea79eb5ccaa5ea765730ca99e146e54a3c0812f9

commit_message:
Use basepython instead of baseversion

Baseversion is not compatible with tox 1.7
so use basepython instead.

And also fix python3 issue to pass gate

Related-Bug: #1376691

Change-Id: Ia9f60388f275e86febb890d5d1b66663a0089ff7

commit_message:
Cleanup translation files

Translations might become stale and obsolete over time, let's cleanup
slowly:
* Remove empty translations files (those were added by accident in the
  past or content gets removed over time)
* Remove files that have less than 20 per cent translated content.

Change-Id: I0c3f6de436d342d032fa38ce2df8a90dd878ea08

commit_message:
V2 token from trust cannot be generated with user/password

Currently, trust handling in the v2 authentication path only exists
for token authentication. This patch add trust support for
user/password authentication.

Change-Id: I71eb45518d3eb5f62c0d18a4083684107a119a9b
Closes-Bug: #1331884

[{'created': '2014-09-25 15:25:46.000000000', 'message': "Add a pool_group to pools in v1.1

Pools can't be grouped together based on type, region or anything. This
is bad for a couple of things but probably the most critical effect is
that when adding pools of different types, the algorithm will balance
across all existing pools regardless of their type.

This patch adds a group field to pools. The group field's default value
is None so that it is backwards compatible for v1 and to avoid forcing
operators to set a group when they simply don't care.

In addition to the above, this patch makes flavors use the pool group
instead of the pool name. This allow us to have multiple pools baking a
specific flavor. Moreover, this also allows us to balance a flavor
across of registered pools and it's the base of the future queue
migrations work.

Change-Id: Ibeba39725ddbc1bc82d4e9d5bceff8b9d69d5839
Closes-bug: #1373994

commit_message:
Add a pool_group to pools in v1.1

Pools can't be grouped together based on type, region or anything. This
is bad for a couple of things but probably the most critical effect is
that when adding pools of different types, the algorithm will balance
across all existing pools regardless of their type.

This patch adds a group field to pools. The group field's default value
is None so that it is backwards compatible for v1 and to avoid forcing
operators to set a group when they simply don't care.

In addition to the above, this patch makes flavors use the pool group
instead of the pool name. This allow us to have multiple pools baking a
specific flavor. Moreover, this also allows us to balance a flavor
across of registered pools and it's the base of the future queue
migrations work.

commit_message:
Add a read-only property for Queues

Queue's name is currently a private attribute in the Queue object. Since
this attribute may need to be accessed, this patch adds a read-only
property that returns the value of the private attribute.

Change-Id: I175d6e2d3b8990f8dbea3c44351143067efacff3

commit_message:
Support having different templates for different releases

We want to adjust the template for Kilo, so rename template.rst to
$release-template.rst and update the tests.

commit_message:
Does chown recursively

Does chown -R on /etc/XXXXX for openstack services
since sometimes there might be files owned by
different account.

Change-Id: Id4b2569e505a59514e565f05d911cdb867902a20
Closes-Bug: 1367263

commit_message:
try out new src libs job on pbr

Add non voting tempest-dsvm-src-pbr job. This tests that proposed
commits to pbr git will work with current master server projects, but
with all the libraries installed from pypi.

This is our canary in the coal mine for the single library from git
approach to forward compatibility testing (i.e. prerelease testing a
library against projects.)

Change-Id: Ib227be8e75cc5f60006176a288260d352be04eec

commit_message:
Improve efficiency of the redis driver when posting messages

Rather than using a watch transaction to rank messages, this patch
modifies the Redis driver's message controller so that it will
use a Lua script. This will avoid retries and MessageConflict errors
under high concurrency.

Change-Id: Idb020ab5b949da5f0bbbfdf3919c217e18bfdc9e

commit_message:
Move Redis driver's claim transaction to Lua

This avoids having to set a watch and retry if someone else beats us to
the punch; the retry is less efficient than doing it with Lua, and would
require adding a backoff sleep to avoid lots of failed requests under
high concurrency.

This patch also adds a Redis server version check in the driver since
Lua requires redis-server >= 2.6

Change-Id: I0c34e267a6358965a54179a4b2fd03ac15b194e9
Closes-Bug: #1372510

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This can cause docs jobs to fail if the project errors out on
warnings.

Change-Id: If97dd51370f25598d39abe876f09d005a0df0172
Related-Bug: #1368910
"}]
commit_message:
Stop using intersphinx

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This can cause docs jobs to fail if the project errors out on
warnings.

Change-Id: If97dd51370f25598d39abe876f09d005a0df0172
Related-Bug: #1368910

commit_message:
cells: make reserve_percent reserve whole hosts

Restore the original intent of reserve_percent. The idea is to keep some
hosts free to allow for resizes and maintenance within a cell.

WIP

Change-Id: I3b3976e380d19e3f83caaa720928ac2f504bcd49
Closes-Bug: #1376681

commit_message:
Replace screen_it() with run_process() throughout

run_process will use screen if USE_SCREEN=True (the default),
otherwise it will simply start the requested service. Therefore
wherever screen_it used, run_process can be instead.

Where stop_screen was found it has been replaced with stop_process.

A tail_log function has been added which will tail a logfile in a
screen if USE_SCREEN is True.

lib/template has been updated to reflect the use of the new
functions.

When using sg the quoting in run_process gets very complicated.
To get around this run_process and the functions it calls accepts
an optional third argument. If set it is a group to be used with sg.

Conflicts:
	functions-common
	lib/ceilometer
	lib/keystone
	lib/neutron
	lib/sahara
	lib/zaqar
	stack.sh

Change-Id: Ia3843818014f7c6c7526ef3aa9676bbddb8a85ca
(cherry picked from commit 2f27a0ed3c609bfcd6344a55c121e56d5569afc9)

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-30 13:52:54.000000000', 'message': 'Run processes without screen

This introduces new run_process() and screen_service() functions and sets the
groundwork to change how DevStack starts services.  screen_service() is simply a
direct call to the screen portion of the old screen_it() function and is intended
to run commands that only need to run under screen, such as log file watchers.

run_process() is a replacement for screen_it() (which remains until all of the
services are updated).  The usage is similar but requires updates to every current
screen_it() call to remove everything that requires the command to be interpreted
by a shell.

The old run_process() and _run_process() functions are still present as
old_run_process() and _old_run_process() to support the deprecated screen_it()
function.  These will all go away in the future once all services have been
confirmed to have been changed over.

There is a similar new set of stop process functions stop_process() and
screen_stop_service().  The old screen_stop() will also remain for the deprecation
period.

As an initial test/demostration this review also includes the changes for
lib/cinder to demonstrate what is required for every service.

I included the scripts I used to test this; tests/fake-service.sh and
tests/run-process.sh are quite rough around the edges and may bite.  They should
mature into productive members of the testing ecosystem someday.

Conflicts:
	functions-common
	lib/cinder

Change-Id: I03322bf0208353ebd267811735c66f13a516637b
(cherry picked from commit 3159a821c2e0662278746c5311e187bcfd4d8b75)

commit_message:
Run processes without screen

This introduces new run_process() and screen_service() functions and sets the
groundwork to change how DevStack starts services.  screen_service() is simply a
direct call to the screen portion of the old screen_it() function and is intended
to run commands that only need to run under screen, such as log file watchers.

run_process() is a replacement for screen_it() (which remains until all of the
services are updated).  The usage is similar but requires updates to every current
screen_it() call to remove everything that requires the command to be interpreted
by a shell.

The old run_process() and _run_process() functions are still present as
old_run_process() and _old_run_process() to support the deprecated screen_it()
function.  These will all go away in the future once all services have been
confirmed to have been changed over.

There is a similar new set of stop process functions stop_process() and
screen_stop_service().  The old screen_stop() will also remain for the deprecation
period.

As an initial test/demostration this review also includes the changes for
lib/cinder to demonstrate what is required for every service.

I included the scripts I used to test this; tests/fake-service.sh and
tests/run-process.sh are quite rough around the edges and may bite.  They should
mature into productive members of the testing ecosystem someday.

Conflicts:
	functions-common
	lib/cinder

commit_message:
doc: Improve use of the support_status attribute

This patch adds admonitions to the template_guide to indicate support
status of resources to the reader. Deprecated resources will be clearly
indicated, as well as the version in which a resource appeared.

This patch also rework the generated markup to use paragraph nodes
instead of inline nodes inside notes.

Closes-Bug: #1360561
Change-Id: I5ee9fd47f0aa9627beb842dc46aa3bac10060e13

commit_message:
Add unit tests covering single operations to ODL

This commit adds the remaining test cases (create and update
operations) to fully cover sync_single_resource. It also defines the
filter_* methods as static or class methods and removes their duplicate
arguments.

Conflicts:
        neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/mechanism_odl.py

Closes-Bug: #1325184
Change-Id: Ic50ddbf32402a9883721d8579c9ccdd53779573b
(cherry picked from commit 903e2a8cd1dd9169048d1ad9dd8a566b2ae52395)

Beside I re Thomas' wording corrections, I would also like to suggest the following:

as currently Cinder supports only unique attachment (and I am not aware of any plans to change this), the "attachments" attribute will return either an empty list or a list of length 1. Would it make sense then do name this attribute in singular - "attachment" and return that single element of the list or None (or even better a similar dict with empty fields) if the list is empty? IMO that would be less boilerplate for user to code in order to get the real attachment data, e.g.

  get_attr: [volume, attachments, 0, server_id]

looks kind of odd with this 0 when there can only be 0, while

  get_attr: [volume, attachment, server_id]

looks cleaner and more intuitive.'}, {'account_id': 8289, 'date': '2014-09-24 01:55:26.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

(3 comments)

Thanks Pavlo Shchelokovskyy:
I don't think need to get the first element of the attachments list, there is a bp about the shared volume(though it's in discuss):https://blueprints.launchpad.net/cinder/+spec/shared-volume, I believe that volume can be attach to several instances one day, and then the length of attachments will gr than 1. And I think there has a reson for attachment designed as list type."}, {'account_id': 8289, 'date': '2014-09-24 04:17:26.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-24 05:23:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
Fix neutron client to catch 404 exceptions

When network services such as lbaas, fwaas or vpnaas are disabled
in neutron, the discovery continues to poll the api calls and gets
back a not found exception. The fix here is to catch the exception
so it doesn't go unhandled.

Change-Id: I8f350b9009f0d8c172836b1dd1123e966f887fdb

commit_message:
Removes deprecated net_common module

Module net_common was replaced by module net_resources as part of migration of
scenario tests to tempest clients.
This patch fixes a few rogue references and removes this module completely.

Change-Id: I5426e030895d219ac456b3cceb361675c839b876
Partially-implements: bp/tempest-client-scenarios

commit_message:
Drop client_type for auth module

Client type was designed to allow the auth module to consume
the official keystone client for tests based on the official clients.
Scenario tests have been migrated to tempest client, and CLI tests
are being moved out of tempest, and they don't need an external
auth provider anyways.
There's no need for client_type anymore, removing it.

Change-Id: I6eebd80ea2259b72e8013e65e9a83615f86a3f84
Partially-implemnts: bp/tempest-client-scenarios

commit_message:
Add an internal test method for rebooting a server

test_reboot_server_hard and test_reboot_server_soft contain almost
the same code and they are redundant.
This patch adds an internal test method and makes them use the method
for cleanup.

Change-Id: I98fc519b5bb2de8cc47007ba9138247f4c0f3369

commit_message:
Introduce NeutronNetworkDeploymentSerializer

Neutron attributes serialization is moved from NetworkManager to
NeutronNetworkDeploymentSerializer.
Versioning is introduced in NeutronNetworkDeploymentSerializer.

Closes-Bug: #1357298

Change-Id: Icac7089fedae9cc525d0d4b3658507745916260c

commit_message:
Override Error Message in Create Subnet Workflow

The Admin->Networks->Create Subnet and Project->Networks->Create Subnet
both inherited their error message from the Project->Create Network
workflow, this patch moves the error message into a instance variable
that can be overridden by sub-classes, and overrides it in the Create
Subnet workflow.

Change-Id: I87e9b89b68560291e389a24be86f788167c5d149
Closes-Bug: 1375783

commit_message:
libvirt: convert HostStateTestCase to avoid DB usage

The HostStateTestCase test case does not do anything DB
related. Convert it to NoDBTestCase to avoid DB setup penalty.
This improves perf from 1.7s to 0.2s

Partial-bug: #1369516
Change-Id: I0b1030b8a4e8c32f24c5b3a08ff86fa5bad06937

commit_message:
libvirt: split firewall tests out into test_firewall.py

The test_driver.py test module had a couple of classes which
were testing functionality from firewall.py. Since test_driver.py
is a really huge file, it is better for the firewall class tests
to live in a separate test_firewall.py module

Related-bug: #1369516
Change-Id: Ibb347780b7b79521ce87b08023771381726b0d53

2. This patch doesn't have RSpec tests"}, {'account_id': 9387, 'date': '2014-10-01 15:32:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

If you want to change upstream code then please also update specs and propose the change to https://github.com/stackforge/puppet-ceilometer upstream project. Otherwise we'll have a lot of problems syncing our manifests with the upstream in the future.

As a quick workaround, you can add "ceilometer_config {'DEFAULT/api_paste_config'...}" in openstack::ceilometer class and not change 'ceilometer' class at all. But it's better to do it in ceilometer::api and push into upstream.'}, {'account_id': 7732, 'date': '2014-10-02 11:06:13.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

there was problem with this parameter  when we had old version of ceilometer package (with old code). Now, when all ceilometer packages are updated, we don't need in that fix."}]

commit_message:
Keep gnocchi/__init__.py empty

Keep gnocchi/__init__.py to avoid to have the whole gnocchi
code loaded even a submodule don't need it.

Specialy for the ceilometer middleware that don't use gnocchi code at
all.

Change-Id: Ic3986aed1ab2f3c5374df410d447c7eb3a931753

commit_message:
Fix $DISTRO_NAME usage for centos7 element

In both of the changed files in this patch, the $DISTRO_NAME usage
is checking against "centos".  The valid value for the centos7
element for $DISTRO_NAME is "centos7"[1].

[1] http://git.io/8IvuTw

Change-Id: I0c4a4b2ecf87c7a9283d10071f6feb494a6c716a

commit_message:
Use unique passwords for replication user

Generates a unique user with a random password for each slave.
The replication user and password is passed to each slave during
the snapshot attach process.  Replication user is deleted from
both the master and the slave during the detach process.

Co-Authored-By: Nikhil Manchanda <SlickNik@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Denis Makogon <dmakogon@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: I9cb158a161714bfff90225227f5c652120393ba7
Closes-bug: 1357065

commit_message:
Display only reachable IP as Floating IP association target

In Neutron deployments some VM port can be unreachable from
external network and cannot be associated with floating IP.
It is confusing if these ports are listed in Floating IP
Associate form.

Change-Id: I2d8faf0dbf4490d198b883fe1becfd950b1b4d14
Closes-Bug: #1252403

commit_message:
ssl_for_create_admin_client

Allowing the use of 'ssl' and 'public' parameters
in _create_admin_client() to emulate _create_keystone_endpoint.

Also altering intialize_for_swift() and initialize_for_heat()
to also use/pass these parameters for their calls to
_create_admin_client().

Change-Id: Ia389c401f3a005c8c457194b78e45f26c5251e1e

commit_message:
Drop OfficialClientManager and references to it

OfficialClientManager is unused now that scenario tests use
clients.Manager instead. Dropping the class, the hacking
rule that forbade its use in API tests and related unit tests.

Change-Id: Ib359b9ab0a903436d9d9c265e8c4d82bdd80a496

It's not possible to guarantee that any particular configuration will work, without trying it.  And even now it's possible to specify a system that cannot be brought up.  Trivially so if, for example, you just don't supply enough machines of the right spec in nodes.json.

The purpose of this spec is to give deployers who need it more flexibility in how their overcloud is deployed.  Such deployers should know and be able to describe their systems well enough. People who don't need this can continue using the default behaviour.  I do think we have a responsibility to give good documentation to help deployers, and possibly _some_ sanity-checking.  But to avoid the possibility of user error entirely is a forlorn hope, I think."}, {'account_id': 9420, 'date': '2014-07-18 17:04:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

commit_message:
Targeted node deployment with capabilities/flavors

Deployers of tripleo may have heterogeneous hardware which they would like to
use effectively.  This spec describes a mechanism for allowing specific nodes
in tripleo to be targeted for specific roles, by exposing Ironic's nodes'
capabilities to Nova's ComputeCapabilitiesFilter, allowing them to be referred
to by extra_specs in Nova flavors.

Describes bp targeted-node-spec

Change-Id: Iafd37688473f954dac0e84b20d335d81ba027ece

commit_message:
Amending the quickstart guide

*Updating to avoid use of manage.py directly.
*Making it more DevStack friendly.
*Adding a sample DevStack local.conf to allow for exercise Horizon
 against more services.
*Added simple developer instructions so new developers aren't tempted
 to work on the DevStack instance of Horizon.

Change-Id: I0840c63183e7cec3b08e4f2ce208479ff7552f60

Get rid of hardcode of styles.less file and make it possible to load
all .less files, including ones in plugins

Add a call to management.validate(task)

calling get_sensor_data.

commit_message:
Don't create IptablesManager on RouterInfo's init

RouterInfo is a class that contains variables which help keep the state
of each router added to the l3 agent. Currently the constructor of
RouterInfo also initializes a new IptablesManager instance, which is
not needed for every RouterInfo instance (thus adding a rather large
overhead). This patch adds a new function to specifically initialize
the ri.iptables_manager variable after the creation of a new RouterInfo.

This change is required for dependent patches, which need to access the
ri.ns_name attribute, but don't need the iptables_manager.

Related-bug: #1374946
Related-bug: #1374947
Change-Id: I9a53f3105764c5dda2a4a57df37d7126ec3a0ca7

remove openvswitch plugin

This changeset removes the openvswitch plugin, but retains the agent for ML2
The database models were not removed since operators will need to migrate the
data.

Stephanie makes an interesting point. My initial thought was 'should we pull this out to some standard location 'case $ARCH in ... esac' since it is repeated in 3 different places. Coupled with Stephanie's point about including more eventualities as allowed/used by Nova this makes more sense.

However in the end I'm not convinced we should do either. James is fixing a specific perceived 'bug' which is that 'some people expect to be able to use 'x86_64' to specify arch.' (myself included). From personal experience I've not really expected to be as specific as 'i486'. But this is just imo."}, {'account_id': 8449, 'date': '2014-09-25 06:43:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

one more point, is it worth adding anote to ./scripts/devtest_testenv.sh ~L92 (comments about node arch and expected values)'}, {'account_id': 10239, 'date': '2014-09-25 12:43:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 9453, 'date': '2014-09-30 21:24:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

I'm also of two minds about the addition of i686

From the point of view of being liberal in what we accept but conservative in what we emit, I think it makes sense for us to take the broadest possible range of inputs -so I do think it makes sense to add in i686 as an input.

From the point of view of making minimal possible changes - it seem like there's a strong reason for us to add in the change that's being made here, because that value is used in other places and we're being inconsistent by not allowing it here. There's less reason for adding in support for i686 because it seems like that's not in use elsewhere.

I think on balance, I'd like for the extra input to be added if there's another revision of this change, but I'm fine with it landing as-is as well, so I'm giving this a +!"}, {'account_id': 9369, 'date': '2014-10-01 07:04:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-24 18:03:07.000000000', 'message': 'Support passing x86_64 to create-nodes

x86_64 is the canonicalized arch for amd64 in Nova[1]. I think it makes
sense to make create-nodes (and thus our UI) a bit friendlier by making
it as an accepted arch value. This will allow for the baremetal flavor
to be created with x86_64 set as cpu_arch in the extra_specs so that if
folks happened to register nodes with x86_64 instead of amd64 in Ironic,
the flavor matching will work.

commit_message:
Support passing x86_64 to create-nodes

x86_64 is the canonicalized arch for amd64 in Nova[1]. I think it makes
sense to make our scripts (and thus our UI) a bit friendlier by making
it as an accepted arch value. This will allow for the baremetal flavor
to be created with x86_64 set as cpu_arch in the extra_specs so that if
folks happened to register nodes with x86_64 instead of amd64 in Ironic,
the flavor matching will work.

[1] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/nova/tree/nova/compute/arch.py#n156

Change-Id: I0f207a5b190bc2df86bc58fc62abc5ac6a93d73f

commit_message:
Fixes session timeout string in horizon

1) This patch fixes the session timeout string problem which
occurs when users clicks on the UI and Ui redirects the
user to the login page but without session timeout message.

2) This patch also fixes other cases of unnecessary logout
messages.

Closes-Bug: #1231355

Change-Id: I9824db44382247d64cc8c399eb5e855e818e8781

commit_message:
Add tests for list_stacks and count_stacks params

There are no tests for show_deleted and show_nested
params in list_stacks and no test for show_deleted
param in count_stacks. Methods' return depends on
these params, so this patch test correct using of
these params.

Change-Id: I08a68ac7c1b1f5abeeadf8563a6b347ecee6e369

commit_message:
Remove unused cache functions from token.core

With the move of functionality from token.core to token.persistence
the cache functions and import are no longer needed in token.core.

Change-Id: I97c96fff64b5c952155c4054df05b1b3ec3a83c5

commit_message:
Move object-store commands to low-level API

api.object_store.APIv1 now contains the formerly top-level functions
implementing the object-store REST client. This replaces the old-style
ObjectClientv1 that is no longer necessary.

Change-Id: I7d8fea326b214481e7d6b24119bd41777c6aa968

subject: Add low-level API base class

commit_message:
Add low-level API base class

Adds the foundation of a low-level REST API client.  This is the final prep
stage in the conversion of the object-store commands from the old restapi
interface to the keystoneclient.session-based API.

* api.api.BaseAPI holds the common operations

Change-Id: I8fba980e3eb2d787344f766507a9d0dae49dcadf

commit_message:
Use appropriate key instead of "pm_*"

In nodes.register_ironic_node method, driver_info is assigned from
"pm_*" keys. But it's not appropriate key name for ironic driver.
This fixes it.

Change-Id: Ibeead2f472b4af91003b52e14628f7854ac3acf1
Closes-Bug: #1367586

Allow user specified endpoint_type in config

* Use user specified endpoint_type (public|internal|admin) for creating
  openstack clients in Rally

Fixed volumes configuration in spark plugin

Only current node group config should influence on data location.

I think the current text is understandable.

However, I think the usage of the term "provider" is an unnecessary complexity.  What this text shows is different ways to make a nested stack.  They all produce the same result when viewed by a user through the Heat API: a single resource that behaves (as seen through the API (remember that an API user can get into the nested stack and explore it like any other stack), and in terms of what it does) like a stack created from the specified template and inputs.  The only differences are in small surface details (type name and properties syntax) of the resource.  I think the term "nested stack" is much more transparent to users.  While the "provider" term may have some historical currency among heat developers, that alone is not a good reason to foist it upon users.'}, {'account_id': 4715, 'date': '2014-09-22 00:34:06.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-22 00:51:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Verified+1

commit_message:
layout: Use default puppet builder for puppet-vswitch

puppet-vswitch is now fully integrated in puppet-openstack team, let use
default builders for puppet-vswitch too. This patch remove non-voting
checks (lint, syntax) and add standard checks.

Change-Id: I66a56db1dca205257973df22d5a9006facd713e8

commit_message:
Remove "nova-manage flavor list" CLI test

The "nova-manage flavor" sub-commands were deprecated in Juno and Nova
change I1798c8a0697009b3dcebeb818580c8323880e395 removes them.

This removes the test_flavor_list test and changes the test_debug_flag
and test_verbose_flag tests to use 'nova-manage service list' instead of
'nova-manage flavor list'.

Change-Id: I4e2399f2fbab2c20299dd62c104b9220c1d36fb2

commit_message:
Fix pid file location to avoid I->J changes that break metadata

Changes in commit 7f8ae630b87392193974dd9cb198c1165cdec93b moved
pid files handled by agent/linux/external_process.py from
$state_path/external/<uuid>.pid  to $state_path/external/<uuid>/pid
that breaks the neutron-ns-metadata-proxy respawn after upgrades
becase the l3 or dhcp agent can't find the old pid file so
they try to start a new neutron-ns-metadata-proxy which won't
succeed, because the old one is holding the port already.

Closes-Bug: #1376128
Change-Id: Id166ec8e508aaab8eea35d89d010a5a0b7fdba1f

commit_message:
Unbundle bootstrap and use xstatic version

This uses the xstatic-packaged versions of bootstrap and bootstrap-datepicker.
It requires newer versions of pyscss and django-pyscss, as there were some
bugs in there that were just fixed upstream.

Change-Id: I0a7660d29fecde915eb46916453a9ea96296798d
Implements: bluperint remove-javascript-bundling
Closes-bug: #1375883

commit_message:
Add docs environment to tox.ini

As per the governance resolution https://review.openstack.org/119875,
projects should have a docs environment in their tox.ini testing
interface. Add one.

Change-Id: Ib3548bc23713e120089ae29b5c4e851de48cf8d3
(cherry picked from commit 81fa6c7b4bd5a1d57cc095395b9d2ba3eeb6c20f)

commit_message:
Update the Elastic Data Processing (EDP) documentation page

* Add description of MapReduce.Streaming job type
* Add description of Spark job type
* Add reference to advanced configuration for Swfit proxy
* Note that .sahara suffix is added to Swift URLs automatically
* A few minor changes

Closes-Bug: 1374574
Closes-Bug: 1374606
Change-Id: Ie53888975ce436439cc808b2fdc45dff66bae1a9

Add test list_servers_filtered_by_name_regex

The nova servers API supports full regex filtering on names. Add a test
for basic regex support.

commit_message:
Skip newly added ec2 test test_run_reboot_terminate_instance

The ec2 test test_run_reboot_terminate_instance allowed us to discover
bug #1352341. It looks like this test discovered a previously unknown
nova EC2 bug.  Disable this test until the underlying bug is fixed.

test_run_reboot_terminate_instance added in:
Ifbd8607566961dbf32b40f34ff603f712d856f6a

Change-Id: I9b64eace84767f6917f82e5657c433074a592fc0
Related-Bug: #1352341

commit_message:
Updated dev guide to include feedback from previous tech review

Changed UTF-8 to plain-text under call sequence
Updated Content Type header to payload_content_type
Rewrote call sequence descriptions for clarity
Changed title caps to sentence caps
Removed cq-devguide.wdl, which was added by mistake

Author: Constanze Kratel

Change-Id: Iffeb69f2fbe8820fcb3f48190316b1f510787a3d

commit_message:
Description of job config hints in new doc page is wrong

The 'configs' field is not a dictionary, it is actually
a list of dictionaries.  Update the description.

Closes-Bug: #1357615
Change-Id: I540abe050f1d81e36f4b5dcca547a7e5c3514c84

[{'created': '2014-08-31 23:48:48.000000000', 'message': "Rename subunit_log.txt to testrepository.subunit

Subunit is not a text protocol - it tunnels itself in stdout, but
that is not the same thing. The .txt extension leads to bad headers
from Apache:

wget -S http://logs.openstack.org/.../logs/subunit_log.txt.gz
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Date: Sun, 31 Aug 2014 23:40:07 GMT
Server: Apache/2.2.22 (Ubuntu)
Vary: Accept-Encoding
Keep-Alive: timeout=5, max=100
Connection: Keep-Alive
Transfer-Encoding: chunked
Content-Type: text/plain

which are clearly bogus - and worse cause wget and curl to treat this
as a plain text file - so they apply line ending transformations to it
which breaks the contents. Some browsers are smarter when one does
'save link' - but all in all its a poor thing to present a binary
object as text.

Don't be confused by the lack of Content-Encoding on the object - thats a
separate issue.

Change-Id: Iacb501e8615a184424f865561cac18c5aa1da1f0
"}]
commit_message:
Rename subunit_log.txt to testrepository.subunit

Subunit is not a text protocol - it tunnels itself in stdout, but
that is not the same thing. The .txt extension leads to bad headers
from Apache:

wget -S http://logs.openstack.org/.../logs/subunit_log.txt.gz
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Date: Sun, 31 Aug 2014 23:40:07 GMT
Server: Apache/2.2.22 (Ubuntu)
Vary: Accept-Encoding
Keep-Alive: timeout=5, max=100
Connection: Keep-Alive
Transfer-Encoding: chunked
Content-Type: text/plain

which are clearly bogus - and worse cause wget and curl to treat this
as a plain text file - so they apply line ending transformations to it
which breaks the contents. Some browsers are smarter when one does
'save link' - but all in all its a poor thing to present a binary
object as text.

Don't be confused by the lack of Content-Encoding on the object - thats a
separate issue.

Change-Id: Iacb501e8615a184424f865561cac18c5aa1da1f0

commit_message:
remove linuxbridge plugin

This changeset removes the linuxbridge plugin, but retains the agent for ML2.
The database models were not removed since operators will need to migrate the
data.

Additionally, the ml2 migration script was altered to support Juno.  For
testing, a user must either run the migration against the icehouse
scheme or run the update, manually change alembic_version to juno and
then run the migration script.  Once the juno migration is added, this
manually step will not be required.

Change-Id: I70689b4247947e6dc08e80fd9b31da9dc691d259
Partial-Bug: 1323729

Add python and pypi jobs for monasca-persister

We are currently working on the necessary files for the build so there is no
need to wait for them to show before making this change

commit_message:
Fix race condition in ISCSIConnector _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi

This is a similar issue as seen in 
https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1375382

The list of devices returned by driver.get_all_block_devices() in
_disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi will potentially contain broken 
symlinks as the SCSI devices have been deleted from calling
self._linuxscsi.remove_multipath_device(device_realpath) right before
_disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi but the udev rule for the symlink 
may not yet have completed.

Adding in a check to os.path.exists() will ensure that we will not 
consider the broken symlinks as an in use device.

Change-Id: I79c9627e9b47127d3765fcec5b7e3bacef179630
Closes-Bug: #1375946

commit_message:
Revert "Remove the update default quotas feature"

This reverts commit ed586a0355fb99a5b1fbeadfc0625f0ceffe8b72.

The quota_class subcommand in python-novaclient was used to set default
quota values so it shouldn't have been removed. As now it is being
restored, the defaults quota panel is being restored too.

Related mailing list thread on the topic:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2014-May/035383.html

Resolved merge conflicts by hand in:
openstack_dashboard/api/cinder.py
openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/info/tabs.py
openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/info/tests.py

Updated translatable segments to match refactors in
openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/defaults/workflows.py
openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/defaults/tables.py

Fixed most egregious post-merge styling errors in
openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/defaults/templates/defaults/index.html
(probably should have been separate, but I just couldn't let it out that way!)

Removed unrelated file that was allowed to be part of the original commit
doc/source/topics/settings.rst

Co-Authored-By: Doug Fish <drfish@us.ibm.com>
Change-Id: Ic4c4ecec843c7ea9afd0db36ce0eb15952da15b3
Partial-Bug: #1299517

commit_message:
Test top-to-bottom: object-store containers

Replicate the object-store container command tests but use requests_mock
to test the entire stack down to the requests module.

These will be useful regressions tests when the existing object-store lib
modules are moved to the low-level API object.

Change-Id: Ibf25be46156eb1009f1b66f02f2073d3913b846d

commit_message:
Allow heat standalone to work devstack stack

For functional testing of heat-standalone it is desirable for
heat to orchestrate on the rest of the cloud which is brought up
by devstack. This change makes the following changes to enable
this when HEAT_STANDALONE=True:

- Don't register the orchestration endpoint or create any dedicated
  heat accounts
- Install and configure the heat keystone V2 auth plugin instead of
  the default v3
- set heat.conf [clients_heat] url so that heat can call its own
  API when no orchestration endpoint is registered
- Modify create_userrc.sh to set the required heat client env
  variables to work with the standalone heat

Change-Id: Idae33bf1a9d550e2575e6390d2d7c8d3b94c401d

commit_message:
Ensure files are closed promptly when generating a key pair

On Python's without reference counting (e.g. PyPy) the current code will keep
the file descriptors open for an arbitrary length of time, until the GC runs.

Change-Id: Idf81df95894fed1d13a68705ef490d5a29367ff1

commit_message:
Update ironic states and documentation

This adds doc strings for the various states, and updates the documentation
header to reflect the current state of states.

In addition, this removes the following unused states:
  - INIT
  - BUILDING
  - SUSPEND

Change-Id: I917f1819066520a81cfaac1c9e884a1bf359d59c
Closes-Bug: #1370184

commit_message:
Add "reboot_instance" EC2 API test

Currently, in "tempest/thirdparty/boto/test_ec2_instance_run.py",
no test case present to test the "reboot_instance" api, similar
to stop_instance, terminate_instance, etc.

Closes-Bug: #1352341

Change-Id: Ifbd8607566961dbf32b40f34ff603f712d856f6a

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Gerrit_Workflow

Adds openSUSE support for developer documentation

Support for openSUSE documentation is updated in this patch.

Change-Id: Id238900382e574836f7832e6907a3e51d62f859d

[{'created': '2014-10-02 01:13:18.000000000', 'message': 'Ensure nova-common is installed before ceilometer

Ceilometer depends on the nova user and group being
present. This change adds a dependency to nova-common
to ensure that packging will handle the user before
the ceilometer compute agent tries to add user ceilometer

Fixes bug 1350980

Change-Id: Iaf950c4a487b4b25c9053d59cab4fa45a1f7390b
'}]
owner_name: Chris Hoge (not involved in upstream development)
commit_message:
Ensure nova-common is installed before ceilometer

Ceilometer depends on the nova user and group being
present. This change adds a dependency to nova-common
to ensure that packging will handle the user before
the ceilometer compute agent tries to add user ceilometer
to the nova group.

Fixes bug 1350980

Change-Id: Iaf950c4a487b4b25c9053d59cab4fa45a1f7390b

commit_message:
console: fix bug when invalid connection info

Fixes bug when checking response returned from the server during
a connection with internal_access_path, if the response's status
is not 200 we should raise the exception.

Closes-Bug: #1375379
Change-Id: Icafcad52cb4e6d9ec4d270e93b89cf13df6b8f61

commit_message:
console: introduce a new exception InvalidToken

Introduces a new exception InvalidToken used when an effectively
invalid token has be sent to a console proxy.
Updates the code to take advantage of this new one.

Change-Id: I9eb18541847e0ce22d5a449268876043ed8eb3a1

commit_message:
Introduce NeutronNetworkDeploymentSerializer

Neutron attributes serialization is moved from NetworkManager to
NeutronNetworkDeploymentSerializer.
Versioning is introduced in NeutronNetworkDeploymentSerializer.

The previous code in network/neutron.py checked specifically for 5.1
environments. This caused 6.0 environments to fall back to the
old behavior and set network_type to 'flat' and configure 'physnet'.

Change-Id: I3940d0910c888794f82dd2159727ef5073367916
Closes-Bug: #1357298

commit_message:
libvirt: convert utils test case to avoid DB usage

The LibvirtUtilsTestCase test case has no need to access the
database. It is also located in the wrong file, as mosts of
the tests for nova.virt.libvirt.utils are in test_utils.py
instead of test_driver.py. Move all the tests into test_utils.py
which already uses NoDBTestCase. This improve performance from
2s to ~0.2s

Partial-bug: #1369516
Change-Id: Id5db3146c524d0208266f754493226856389a722

commit_message:
Don't list entire module autoindex on docs index

Don't list entire api/autoindex under Developer Docs,  we already have a
model index link at the  bottom of the page, showing the entire
autoindex on the home page is makes the page overwhelming.

Change-Id: I25c5b50412881b55aa745ce3da2c22466e879fcf

commit_message:
ZFSSA iSCSI driver cannot add multple initiators to a group

All initiators defined in zfssa_initiator property would be
added to the group.
Also fixed some typos related to initiators error messages.

Change-Id: Iec6c90702e5aafa153b4a7f1e429974ac450afc0
Closes-Bug: #1369750

owner_name: Chris Hoge (not involved in upstream development)
commit_message:
Ensure nova-common is installed before ceilometer

Ceilometer depends on the nova user and group being
present. This change adds a dependency to nova-common
to ensure that packging will handle the user before
the ceilometer compute agent tries to add user ceilometer
to the nova group.

Fixes bug 1350980

Change-Id: If91c5eed28df5f6315490ad30584f6a1d4035f79

commit_message:
Solidify environment_version handling in run_tests.sh

Update the environment_version to be a string, specifically the
gerrit review id to prevent environment_version values from
multiple reviews from getting merged.

Also change the current environment_version to reflect the
last patch to require an update.

Change-Id: I0a966fd1d95459bf344ae4226aca21d326a2b3cb
Closes-Bug: 1376485

'}, {'created': '2014-10-01 07:49:34.000000000', 'message': 'Add "affinity" tracking to nodes and conductors

Add "conductor_affinity" column to nodes table, containing a reference to the
`id` of the conductor service (not its hostname) that has most recently
performed some action which could require local state to be maintained
(eg, built a PXE config, or started a SOL session).

Using the `id` as a foreign key necessitates not deleting conductors
when unregistering them, but instead marking them offline. This also
helps in determining if a conductor service was only restarted (though
this patch does not implement graceful shutdown).

Thus, this patch also adds an "online" boolean column to the conductors
table to track whether a conductor is on- or offline, and updates
the register and unregister methods to use that field transparently.
It may be noted that this does not change the behavior of
register_conductor or unregister_conductor, though an optional
"update_existing" parameter has been added to register_conductor. This
replaces a DELETE query with an UPDATE query instead.

Co-Authored-By: David Shrewsbury <shrewsbury.dave@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Lucas Alvares Gomes <lucasagomes@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Add "affinity" tracking to nodes and conductors

Add "conductor_affinity" column to nodes table, containing a reference to the
`id` of the conductor service (not its hostname) that has most recently
performed some action which could require local state to be maintained
(eg, built a PXE config, or started a SOL session).

Using the `id` as a foreign key necessitates not deleting conductors
when unregistering them, but instead marking them offline. This also
helps in determining if a conductor service was only restarted (though
this patch does not implement graceful shutdown).

Thus, this patch also adds an "online" boolean column to the conductors
table to track whether a conductor is on- or offline, and updates
the register and unregister methods to use that field transparently.
It may be noted that this does not change the behavior of
register_conductor or unregister_conductor, though an optional
"update_existing" parameter has been added to register_conductor. This
replaces a DELETE query with an UPDATE query instead.

Co-Authored-By: David Shrewsbury <shrewsbury.dave@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Lucas Alvares Gomes <lucasagomes@gmail.com>

Related-bug: #1279331
Change-Id: I8e8b5cc00fc9f565ad2fb442e9a26077342e0a25

commit_message:
XenAPI: Upgrade built-VM to Trusty

If you're not using an XVA then the built-VM was previously Saucy, which is
not supported by openstack any more.

Change-Id: I1040d9e43d517582e76f2e1df787986b5ffbc42c

commit_message:
Add unit test for add_floating_ip API

Currently, add_floating_ip API has no unit test for body's key test,
this patch adds the test cases.

Change-Id: I32a32514c68fcd8717011d37724a20993aa8ed20

commit_message:
javelin: fix user destruction

Use the right Python method to destroy an user:
- get the tenant_id
- get the user_id (with tenant_id)
- delete the user using user_id

Change-Id: I2121fedf563cc4d41f8ad8dfcaf55d767d87d69f

[{'created': '2014-07-17 06:09:11.000000000', 'message': "Adjust on_job_posting to not hold the lock while investigating

To avoid issues when investigating jobs in one thread and having
a dispatcher thread get locked on that same investigation lock avoid
this entirely by not holding onto that lock.

This also adds a small cleanup around the notifier thread pool and
ensures that it actually exists in a useable state (and handles the
exceptions that arise when it doesn't) on submission.

Change-Id: I12e71f029726ec54ec0aadbdf71cc3c7a959f047

commit_message:
Adjust on_job_posting to not hold the lock while investigating

To avoid issues when investigating jobs in one thread and having
a dispatcher thread get locked on that same investigation lock avoid
this entirely by not holding onto that lock.

This also adds a small cleanup around the notifier thread pool and
ensures that it actually exists in a useable state (and handles the
exceptions that arise when it doesn't) on submission.

Change-Id: I12e71f029726ec54ec0aadbdf71cc3c7a959f047

commit_message:
Make it so that the import works for older versions of kombu

The import location for message was different in older versions
of kombu, so when using it for mocking we need to take into
account the older location so that the test correctly works out
as it should (without import errors).

Fixes bug 1376330

Change-Id: Ifad489f0e15490168f993f48bfedfd553acd4a69

commit_message:
Handle default string values when using user_enabled_invert

When the user_enabled_invert setting is being used, values returned
from LDAP are ultimately converted to a bool type when we reach the
inversion logic.  If the user_enabled_default value is used due to
no value being returned from LDAP, the type is a string.  This causes
the inversion logic to be evaluated incorrectly, as 'not' will return
False for any non-empty string.  This results in disabled accounts
that should be enabled.

Change-Id: Id7b024c12815748305458ca05fc8f8a6324c1908
Closes-bug: #1376053

Recent changes in the l3 plugin related to dvr
snat binding has changed how the binding is sent
to the l3-agent. This patch changes the l3-agent
to properly handle the external gateway
clear/delete cases.
SNAT namespaces will not be deleted in all cases without this fix.

Change-Id: I051fb97d802b0508b30683a33673b85f5ab24000
Closes-bug: #1373524

commit_message:
fix dvr snat bindings for external-gw-clear

When router_gateway_clear happens, the
schedule_router calls the unbind_snat_servicenode
in the plugin. This will clear the agent binding
from the binding table. But the l3-agent was
expecting the ex_gw_port binding to be present.
The agent needs to check its cache of the
router['gw_host_port'] value now.

Change-Id: I051fb97d802b0508b30683a33673b85f5ab24000
Closes-bug: #1373524

'}, {'created': '2014-09-11 18:17:47.000000000', 'message': "(WIP) Implement base aviator provider

This provider is intended to be used by other providers to provide some
common methods and to pull in the aviator module. This work in progress
implements the authenticate method and some helper methods.

See https://review.openstack.org/#/c/116754 for example provider
implementation using this base provider

Known issues:
1) Can't authenticate with a service token: fixed in aviator, needs a
   release to aimonb/aviator
2) Faraday will complain about system_timer on ruby 1.8. There isn't a
   good way to fix or silence this warning.
3) Puppet::Provider::Aviator#authenticate can't parse the
   admin_endpoint from keystone.conf if it contains a python-formatted
   variable in the string (e.g.
   admin_endpoint=http://localhost:%(admin_port)s/). This was probably
   an issue before this refactor, since the code to parse this value
   was mostly copied from lib/puppet/provider/keystone.rb in the
   keystone module.

TODO:
1) Spec tests need to be written
2) Documentation needs to be added

Questions:
1) Should credentials be passed in a hash in the auth parameter? Or
   should it have individual parameters?
2) Should it check facter values for auth credentials? (device providers
   sometimes do this)

Change-Id: I56b0d07ae8f4738037eda486b75a0f6e24fe80e7
Implements: blueprint use-aviator-in-module-resources

2) Faraday will complain about system_timer on ruby 1.8. There isn't a
   good way to fix or silence this warning.
3) Puppet::Provider::Aviator#authenticate can't parse the
   admin_endpoint from keystone.conf if it contains a python-formatted
   variable in the string (e.g.
   admin_endpoint=http://localhost:%(admin_port)s/). This was probably
   an issue before this refactor, since the code to parse this value
   was mostly copied from lib/puppet/provider/keystone.rb in the
   keystone module.

TODO:
1) Spec tests need to be written
  - started writing tests for #authenticate using vcr
2) Documentation needs to be added

Questions:
1) Should credentials be passed in a hash in the auth parameter? Or
   should it have individual parameters?
2) Should it check facter values for auth credentials? (device providers
   sometimes do this)

Change-Id: I56b0d07ae8f4738037eda486b75a0f6e24fe80e7
Implements: blueprint use-aviator-in-module-resources

"}, {'created': '2014-09-17 06:01:17.000000000', 'message': "Implement base aviator provider

This patch adds a dependency on the aimonb/aviator module and adds
functionality to support interactions with the OpenStack services' API
via aviator.

The patch adds a parent provider that is intended for other providers
to inherit from. The parent provider has methods to authenticate to
openstack services and make requests. The authenticate method can
accept credentials as an argument hash or infer credentials from the
environment.

It also adds a stub type parameter that allows types to incorporate
basic parameters they need in order to support using aviator.

Change-Id: I56b0d07ae8f4738037eda486b75a0f6e24fe80e7
Implements: blueprint use-aviator-in-module-resources

commit_message:
Implement base aviator provider

This patch adds a dependency on the aimonb/aviator module and adds
functionality to support interactions with the OpenStack services' API
via aviator.

The patch adds a parent provider that is intended for other providers
to inherit from. The parent provider has methods to authenticate to
openstack services, create session objects, and make requests. The
authenticate method can accept credentials as an argument hash or infer
credentials from the environment.

It also adds a stub type parameter that allows types to incorporate
basic parameters they need in order to support using aviator.

Change-Id: I56b0d07ae8f4738037eda486b75a0f6e24fe80e7
Implements: blueprint use-aviator-in-module-resources

commit_message:
Add a check making sure getChildAt is not None

Currently, the getText function can throw an exception if the doc
is not None but the getChildAt method returns None.

The method prevents such exception.

Change-Id: Id054a9db80fc0e846e832fc0813020410d2ebe3b

commit_message:
Do not crash with "swift list --lh" for Ceph RadosGW.

If 'x-timestamp' header is not present in 'swift list' result,
date string cannot be correctly generated. Check for correct
exception to catch this case and return a special string value.
This is just a workaround for faulty RadosGW behavior.

Change-Id: I172843a2668e33efac00924906ff0dca3e790050
Closes-Bug: 1349528

commit_message:
Storage for images is not necessarily object

Glance image backend doesn't have to be an object store. In particular, Ceph
RBD is a block storage backend.

Change-Id: Idd60edef5509a5b10e3a3e353ed2505d1508571f

Like the buildfarm spec,  I have some issues with the idea of solum managing long term servers on behalf of a user from a security and general operations POV, especially if we're talking about their master git repo for their source code.

Similarly I think it would make sense to spin up resources for users,  but push the ownership of managing the VMs and the security/uptime/DR to the user ( an operator persona at the tenant level or cloud operator, not the dev ).

Also there was a talk at the last summit ( which I didn't attend ) about hosting storage for git repos on SWIFT that might be interesting - https://www.openstack.org/summit/openstack-summit-atlanta-2014/session-videos/presentation/openstack-swift-as-a-backend-for-git"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-06-30 14:40:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: -Verified

commit_message:
Add docs target and generate api docs

Once we use the pbr based build to generate files, we prune
the indexes to remove references to code we would like to
hide like the common modules and private modules in conf.py.
We reuse the same excluded_patterns variable that is already
used in Sphinx and filter these modules from autoindex.rst

Closes-Bug: #1364140

Change-Id: I5767e429e63935f055a6f4e82349224ccfa2f497

commit_message:
Check that public repos exist before cloning

Our unittest and build scripts use the git CLI to clone
and checkout repos. If a clone of a URL that appears good
results in a 404, git CLI will prompt at the terminal for
a username and password, assuming the repo was not found
because it is private. This causes solum-worker to freeze
indefinitely as it waits for this input.

This patch adds a function to common/utils to check via curl
that a repo is visible to the public, to keep the git CLI
from needlessly asking for credentials. Of course, this patch
also incorporates this utility into unittest-app and build-app.

Closes-Bug: 1375471
Change-Id: Ia133966a77b7f38b0a2617a482ab9223ab8f9b08

[{'created': '2014-10-01 20:54:13.000000000', 'message': 'Do inserts in a more performant way

Use the "on duplicate key" syntax to remove the previous select
before insert. It also allows more than one AlarmCreationBolt to
run concurrently since duplicate creation of metrics was possible
before this change

This requires the change to the schema in
https://review.openstack.org/125490

Change-Id: Ieafa732e822a38ae118037d3c460ce60bce1c36c
'}]
commit_message:
Do inserts in a more performant way

Use the "on duplicate key" syntax to remove the previous select
before insert. It also allows more than one AlarmCreationBolt to
run concurrently since duplicate creation of metrics was possible
before this change

This requires the change to the schema in
https://review.openstack.org/125490

Change-Id: Ieafa732e822a38ae118037d3c460ce60bce1c36c

commit_message:
Update deprecated Glance CLI

Since this patch has been merged in python-glanceclient 0.14.1:
https://github.com/openstack/python-glanceclient/commit/1dfce5301c5d7cd456c98629a007917120637c8a

We have to update the way to call Glance Client.
This patch updates for glance image-list, image-show and the way to get
a token, and also the way the glance command output is parsed.

Change-Id: If3e1e42b1245dd064fa00e07037535afc9caa04c

commit_message:
Template not required on stack-adopt

With this change, template is not required on stack-adopt and
also parameters from the original stack are adopted.

commit_message:
Enabled mask_password to handle byte code strings

Byte code strings passed into mask_password cause the coersion to
six.text_type to fail with a UnicodeDecodeError.  The code can
work with the byte code string, but the incoming message may be
an i18n object that has to be coerced.

The temporary fix is to ignore the UnicodeDecodeError on the
coersion.   A better solution will be provided for Kilo.

This is related to cinder bug #1368527

Change-Id: I6dd5195d004477f61cc87bf22f3bf5958c78f754
Closes-bug: #1366189
Closes-bug: #1368527

commit_message:
Fix find for resources with id_attribute

The find method had 'id' hard coded rather than using id_attribute.
The error message printed by find was not correct for resources that
do not have a resource_name, so I added the get_resource_name()
method.

Change-Id: I53965e74bd29081f3c3fa3f1da406aeb71cc2c01

commit_message:
Changes for Alarmed Metrics

This code creates Alarms correctly but can't delete them or
Alarm Definitions. It also does not handle Alarm Definition
updates.

This code is dependent on the new monasca-common changes that
have not been merged.

MetricFilteringBolt reads AlarmDefinitions on startup.
MetricFilteringBolt sends the message that a new MetricDefinition
was found for an AlarmDefinition.

MetricAggregationBolt gets SubAlarm messages for SubAlarm creation
instead of getting SubAlarms from the database

Created the AlarmCreationBolt which will handle AlarmCreation when
the metrics that fill an alarm are seen. Also, will add Alarmed Metrics
to an existing alarm if they match.

Temporarily renamed sub_alarm table to sub_alarms table to not conflict
with API table.

Using the BeanMapper to directly map an AlarmDefinition caused an issue
with the older version of guava used by storm so had to hack around that.

Temporarily renamed sub_alarm table to sub_alarms table to not conflict
with API table.

Using the BeanMapper to directly map an AlarmDefinition caused an issue
with the older version of guava used by storm so had to hack around that.

Allow more then one AlarmCreationBolt because it routes by
AlarmDefinitionId

Change the routing for MetricFilteringBolts so they always get the same
tenantId + Metric name. Prevents multiple messages from going to the
AlarmCreationBolt

Removed MetricDefinitionDAO and all related classes since they are
not used anymore

Make it so there is only one AlarmCreationBolt because there is
no code protection for ensuring dimensions aren't created twice
for concurrent creates

Tests are turned off for now

Change-Id: I6747d789bbe0f7f723e19060bf19c3fe318c1e3e

commit_message:
VMware: Add retype to list of supported operations

Commit 86591a24d48fe19be427b5a8981821fcdb85bb37 added support for
retype API in VMDK driver. Retype allows the user to change the
volume type associated with a volume. This patch updates the list
of supported operations by VMDK driver to include retype.

Change-Id: I4610b86fdf635f26dcdd6ad873caa29b5070e155

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-30 01:26:48.000000000', 'message': "Stop using intersphinx

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This can cause docs jobs to fail if the project errors out on
warnings.

Change-Id: I6d0bb0678ff35a751c0b7c40cb73803701eb8a75
Related-Bug: #1368910
"}]
commit_message:
Stop using intersphinx

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This can cause docs jobs to fail if the project errors out on
warnings.

Change-Id: I6d0bb0678ff35a751c0b7c40cb73803701eb8a75
Related-Bug: #1368910

commit_message:
remove kombu from package lists

This is a pure python library that we should probably let pip
handle so that we don't accidentally only test whatever patched
version is in trusty instead of the upstream versions.

Change-Id: I93d2f9344b9f83d2397466b4bc29c97210919ed9

commit_message:
Declare cinder::glance to set glance_api_version

Prior to syncing upstream cinder module, glance_api_version was set from
cinder::backend::rbd. New upstream moved this to cinder::glance.

Change-Id: Ied9f4308b998e9f345449e03a00221de41261e85
Closes-Bug: #1373096

has been torn down, OSC functional tests should be run when
devstack is up and running.

Change-Id: I7f8f820a0f065db72f62b6de148d7241a5f309e8
'}, {'created': '2014-10-01 01:51:55.000000000', 'message': 'Change OSC functional tests to not unstack

OSC functional tests were incorrectly unstacking devstack,
before the post_gate_hook ran. The functional tests should be
run when devstack is up and running.

Change-Id: I7f8f820a0f065db72f62b6de148d7241a5f309e8
'}]
commit_message:
Change OSC functional tests to not unstack

OSC functional tests were incorrectly unstacking devstack,
before the post_gate_hook ran. The functional tests should be
run when devstack is up and running.

Change-Id: I7f8f820a0f065db72f62b6de148d7241a5f309e8

https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/DocImpact)

commit_message:
Add templates for replica and replica source

This patch adds templates for replica and replica source.
Previously this was hard coded in the code. This gives
deployers the ability to customize their replication
configurations.

Closes-Bug: 1370125

Change-Id: Ie1b4cff1685d2577240eb43ffecac3c977ba964c

commit_message:
Convert unicode to UTF8 when calling ldap.str2dn()

The string passed to ldap.str2dn() needs to be UTF8 encoded, otherwise
we encounter UnicodeEncodeError exceptions.

This patch adds UTF8 encoding where it was missing for ldap.str2dn()
calls as well as some unit tests to cover the functions that were
lacking this encoding step.

Change-Id: I96e718f1d43f4aad272ca4990d3905a5adf1f07d
Closes-bug: #1375139

Hi Alexei,

Listener is not getting garbage collected after stopping server (ie - after calling messaging server 'stop' method) because it is still referenced from connection object. https://github.com/openstack/oslo.messaging/blob/944b947fb8c45061ef434a0fba865b1368eb0334/oslo/messaging/_drivers/amqpdriver.py#L414
To cleanup listener we have to close listener connection explicitly.

Listener will be garbage collected only if we stop service completely (ie- kill service), but when you send 'SIGHUP' signal to service it restarts service. After service restart it creates new listener and old listener is not getting cleaned, because of this messages are not getting processed properly. (If messages comes to old listener then those messages will not be processed as there is no executor running for this listener. We are stopping executor in messaging server 'stop' method)"}, {'account_id': 7763, 'date': '2014-07-11 09:45:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

>Listener is not getting garbage collected after stopping server (ie - after calling messaging server 'stop' method) because it is still referenced from connection object.

Thanks for detailed reply. Your reply is so detailed that it actually contains the answer to the problem. Why not using weakref to remove reference cycle between listener and connection objects? This will allow objects to be deleted and closed normally."}, {'account_id': 8300, 'date': '2014-07-14 05:53:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 8300, 'date': '2014-07-16 10:33:46.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-16 10:33:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-27 16:16:04.000000000', 'message': 'Close listener connection after stopping rpcserver

Currently listener connection is not closed after stoping rpc server.

So when rpc server restarts after receiving SIGHUP signal, it has two
listeners. One which is not closed while stopping and other
which is created while starting the rpc server.

This is causing issue in processing messages properly.

Closes-Bug: #1335086
Change-Id: I1f39eedf1500b6b6209ae0222f32e08e304895e0
'}, {'created': '2014-07-02 06:20:16.000000000', 'message': "Cleanup listener after stopping rpc server

If you don't close the AMQP connection, then the connection
remains open and the next time when the messages are sent on
the listening topic, then some of the messages will not be processed
as there is no dispatcher running to process the message.

Closes-Bug: #1335086
Change-Id: I1f39eedf1500b6b6209ae0222f32e08e304895e0
"}, {'created': '2014-07-04 08:25:37.000000000', 'message': "Cleanup listener after stopping rpc server

If you don't close the AMQP connection, then the connection
remains open and the next time when the messages are sent on
the listening topic, then some of the messages will not be processed
as there is no dispatcher running to process the message.

Closes-Bug: #1335086
Change-Id: I1f39eedf1500b6b6209ae0222f32e08e304895e0
"}, {'created': '2014-07-16 10:33:46.000000000', 'message': 'Removing cyclic reference of listener object

After stopping messaging server, listener object is not garbage
collected as it is still referenced by the connection object.
Passing listener object as a weak ref proxy object to the
connection will automatically garbage collect listener which
will close the connection.

Closes-Bug: #1335086
Change-Id: I1f39eedf1500b6b6209ae0222f32e08e304895e0

commit_message:
Cleanup listener after stopping rpc server

If you don't close the AMQP connection, then the connection
remains open and the next time when the messages are sent on
the listening topic, then some of the messages will not be processed
as there is no dispatcher running to process the message.

Closes-Bug: #1335086
Change-Id: I1f39eedf1500b6b6209ae0222f32e08e304895e0

commit_message:
Add VNIC_TYPE in the portbinding for OpenContrail plugin

This patch adds the VNIC_TYPE for the OpenContrail plugin
when the port is created.
Nova expects VNIC_TYPE when it creates a port during instance
creation.

Change-Id: Ibfa8c5d10aea577c0e08b3e6256122b9946f1504
Closes-bug: #1373872

commit_message:
Identity authentication now uses rotated passwords

A previous commit added the ability to store rotated passwords. The idea
is that the rotated passwords would be valid for authentication for some
configurable period of time. This commit enables those passwords to be
used. A future commit will add the ability to manage those password
through an extension API.

bp password-rotation

Change-Id: Ifc607f881aadae7c571352d38e6f7716a2c48150

subject: Adds table and model for storing rotated passwords

commit_message:
add {pipeline}-tempest-dsvm-src-{name} job template

This job allows us to hand up a single project that will be designated
as project from source. With this we can use the new devstack
refactorings to provide forward testing for libraries so that they can
see that they don't break all of openstack.

Change-Id: Id5ac1517be3a8697063b39fc1fbc0eb35b5ba449

commit_message:
Rework coverage jobs

Remove coverage job from python-jobs since many projects are not setup
for it.

Add the coverage job back to each project where coverage currently
succeeds.

Change-Id: I0e480827a2f1990945b3dff0ab08a5559ff40c03

commit_message:
Improve documentation around usage of cinder-volume-nfs

This change aims at improving the doc around usage of the different
cinder backend elements, particularily cinder-volume-nfs.

We also remove cinder-volume from the BLOCKSTORAGE image elements as
it will be eventually installed as dependency by one of the
cinder-* backend elements.

Change-Id: Id553b15227c0b980702174d7d2a0410ab30dcce4

It doesn't make sense to me since the code reach the image-upload call there should already pass some policy checking code within nova upper layer. Can you share your investigation result with me?
So I'm thinking is the reason nova upload a lot of chunks to glance and this progress it too long to caused auth token expired? If the root cause is this then this approach can not fixes the issue obviously."}, {'account_id': 7531, 'date': '2013-10-24 09:55:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Hi Zhi,

This patch saves the unnecessary upload when the auth token is not valid at the start of the upload.
This is especially common in case of retries.'}, {'account_id': 6549, 'date': '2013-10-24 10:39:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Hi Srideve, thanks for response. I have two questions more:

1. I still interested in what's "retries" case you are saying, actually I'm not see those token expiration issue (before upload image) as a common case in our deployment. What cause the token expired?

2. If it's a common case, why we not fix it in a common place but for xen hypervisor only?'}, {'account_id': 7531, 'date': '2013-10-24 12:20:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

1. This is not a common scenario, but does happen.
* The is a large image (of say 40 chunks)
* Upload returns a 500 and raises a retryable error. 
* During retry, the auth token expires (because, the first try itself took very long).  Only after the whole upload process finishes, it raises a Unauthorised response.
2. We are fixing this starting with xenserver plugin.'}, {'account_id': 4463, 'date': '2013-10-30 14:19:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

I think I'm in agreement with Brian that we shouldn't add another http request if at all possible.  That being said, I'm not sure what the ramifications are for a early http response and whether the glance side is capable of dealing with that easily.  My guess is we would need some changes on this side as well if I understand correctly the proposal.

The fix as proposed doesn't address all cases either?  What if the auth has read access (HEAD?), but not write access (PUT?).

If this is the best option, this still needs some testing around it as it crosses a services interface.   That's my primary -1 relative to my comments/questions."}, {'account_id': 7701, 'date': '2014-04-03 08:40:52.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

And as far as the extra HTTP call, imho I wouldn't be too concerned about performance there as long as we're reusing the same connection for the two calls. I agree that its not the best solution, I'd have preferred having the 100-continue header but as requests doesn't find it relevant at the moment, I don't think we're left with a lot of choice.

Thanks Christopher, for bringing this up. I'd nearly forgotten this bit and for some reason was still foolishly thinking that nova too has moved to python requests and hence doesn't support 100-continue. But yeah, it still uses httplib. 

Now httplib does have support for 100-continue but it does not give you a handle to the intermediate response which is what we basically would be needing. Hence, we had, few months ago, explored the option of pulling in the BufferedHttp which swift uses. Look at the foll patches we'd proposed to swiftclient. 

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/56558/
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/55517/  

I like this approach better. But the other one is fairly simple implementation wise. Thoughts??"}, {'account_id': 8430, 'date': '2014-04-08 18:30:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Thanks for the additional background.  Which implementation do you like better?'}, {'account_id': 7701, 'date': '2014-04-10 10:43:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Well, both have their own list of pros and cons. This approach is pretty straightforward. All it does is, it uses the same connection to fire A HEAD call to check if auth failure happens. if so then retry.  

Where as the other one adds an extra header, and expects a 100-continue response for the PUT call and as soon as you get the CONTINUE, you proceed with sending the data. While this one is cleaner and precise, it has a small issue with regards to implementation which is that we'll have to pull in swifts' bufferedhttp.py. The tricky bit is that the bufferedhttp does a whole lot of things like buffering the reading of headers etc which we dont need. So we'll have to pull in stuff only related to getting a handle to the intermediate response alone. basically the get_expect bit. 

It still is an additional module added. But will keep the code cleaner and readable and hence my personal choice. Thoughts??

PS: Sorry for the verbose reply. Didnt know how to shorten this."}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2014-04-18 06:03:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

[{'created': '2013-10-11 07:24:27.000000000', 'message': 'glance plugin should not upload on unauthorised

The glance plugin tries to upload for invalid auth token.
In nova/image/glance, the X-Auth-Token is taken from the context, and
passed on to upload. And in the upload_tarball method, the plugin starts
to put the headers and upload the image, and only after all the chunks
are uploaded it will receive an UnAuthorized response.This results in an
unnecessary upload of all the chunks.

Fix: Have a "HEAD" call made with the same X-Auth-Token and other
headers. If that returns a 401, then abandon the upload process.
Otherwise, continue with the upload.

Fixes bug Bug #1238393
Change-Id: Ic47e94245980c6f08e56ef28f910a5cde598d2d9

commit_message:
glance plugin should not upload on unauthorised

The glance plugin tries to upload for invalid auth token.
In nova/image/glance, the X-Auth-Token is taken from the context, and
passed on to upload. And in the upload_tarball method, the plugin starts
to put the headers and upload the image, and only after all the chunks
are uploaded it will receive an UnAuthorized response.This results in an
unnecessary upload of all the chunks.

Fix: Have a "HEAD" call made with the same X-Auth-Token and other
headers. If that returns a 401, then abandon the upload process.
Otherwise, continue with the upload.

Fixes bug Bug #1238393
Change-Id: Ic47e94245980c6f08e56ef28f910a5cde598d2d9

commit_message:
Drop OfficialClientManager from tenant isolation

Scenario tests use the tempest clients, so drop support for
OfficialClientManager from the tenant isolation classes.

Change-Id: I84638210043d376b4f4025a69751536651991293
Partially-implements: bp:tempest-client-scenarios

development.

[{'created': '2014-09-30 14:49:41.000000000', 'message': 'Fix parsing of emulated enabled DN

If a non-default emulated enabled DN is specified in configuration,
the DN structure returned from python-ldap is incorrectly converted
to a string.  This leads to an index error when we attempt to extract
the RDN attribute and value.

This patch removes the incorrect string conversion and instead does
the proper conversion on the RDN strings that we extract.

Change-Id: I8f0c4594cfa9a41e1875870c3eb63fae32c8c041
Resolves-bug: #1375772
'}]
commit_message:
Fix parsing of emulated enabled DN

If a non-default emulated enabled DN is specified in configuration,
the DN structure returned from python-ldap is incorrectly converted
to a string.  This leads to an index error when we attempt to extract
the RDN attribute and value.

This patch removes the incorrect string conversion and instead does
the proper conversion on the RDN strings that we extract.

Change-Id: I8f0c4594cfa9a41e1875870c3eb63fae32c8c041
Resolves-bug: #1375772

commit_message:
remove scary error message in tox

Found an interesting cantrip in the devstack tox.ini that gets rid of
the scary can't find bash error message at the beginning of test
runs. Reducing non error looking error things make it easier to see
real errors.

Change-Id: I4e1b826626063bf8d5a15531f5768f9ce0eea6a5

commit_message:
Add bash and find to tox whitelist_externals

Stop triggering a not installed in virtualenv every time
bash or find is called. No need for these unnecessary warnings all over the place.

Change-Id: I32e8916b187f46937f5b5f94ccff8ae68ca34828

commit_message:
move integrated api client to requests library

The integrated api client previously did the HTTPConnection /
HTTPSConnection url parsing dance. In python 2.x HTTPSConnection
doesn't care about SSL certs at all. While not actually an issue for
these tests, it does mean we keep around an example in the code that
uses HTTPSConnection, which will prevent us from creating a hacking
rule to keep those out once the other 4 actual security issues with
HTTPSConnection are removed.

Change-Id: Idd7d5a055600dda663f9c56b39883510f8688b12
Related-Bug: #1188189

commit_message:
Code clean-up due to type order enhancement

Removed code related old Order. Cleaned redundant
fields from Order model. Also cleaned the API, no
more support for old style orders.

- Fixed broken functional test
- Fixed alembic version conflict due to CR 122498

Closes-Bug: 1335171

Change-Id: I33fe7a75568e0108c623e8f6f786fb9e9b888d36

I may be wrong, but at a glance, it looks like the test classes which this patch updates don't actually need a DB fixture - they need an admin context.

Also, I'm wondering why all the DB fixture code is in tests/base, not tests/db/base - but it looks just like legacy from when we forked from Nova. What do you think about separating the "needs admin context" from "needs a db fixture" tests?

I think that would make it much clearer when adding/editing tests in the future.'}, {'account_id': 12356, 'date': '2014-10-01 16:56:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Devananda, thanks for your suggestion, saw your comments in IRC and uploaded this change - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/125361/ . It seems that tests actually need DB fixture, e.g. when using base class without DB fixture in ironic.tests.dhcp.TestNeutron it fails with errors like this one:

OperationalError: (OperationalError) no such table: nodes u'INSERT INTO nodes (created_at, updated_at, id, uuid, instance_uuid, chassis_id, power_state, target_power_state, provision_state, target_provision_state, provision_updated_at, last_error, instance_info, properties, driver, driver_info, reservation, maintenance, console_enabled, extra) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)' ('2014-10-01 16:50:01.956952', None, 123, u'1be26c0b-03f2-4d2e-ae87-c02d7f33c123', None, 42, None, None, None, None, None, None, '{"foo": "bar"}', '{"cpu_arch": "x86_64", "memory_mb": "4096", "cpus": "8", "local_gb": "10"}', u'fake', '{"foo": "bar"}', None, 0, 0, '{}')

While there are actually some tests that need only admin context. You can check it in the second change.'}]
